cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of domain adaptation in pedestrian detection using deep learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes an iterative algorithm and an unsupervised regularizer, which involves machine learning and optimization techniques, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) likely categories as well. The task of pedestrian detection also involves robotics and autonomous systems, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible category. Finally, the paper deals with image and video processing, which falls under cs.MM (Multimedia).
